children.subject: Ah, lovely.  Thanks for pointing that out.  It is currently the "correct" site, but I've emailed Piazza to see if that can be fixed.
Update:  it's fixed.  The link is now https://piazza.com/berkeley/spring2020/compsci189289a or https://piazza.com/class/k5n3zwlu8ly1he.
Heads up pizza link says fall 2020 - I do not know if thats in purpose or you mean spring 2020.

history.content:
CS 189 and CS 289A will take place on Mondays and Wednesdays, 6:30–8:00 pm in Wheeler Hall Auditorium (a.k.a. 150 Wheeler Hall), starting today (January 22). Discussion sections are on Tuesdays and Wednesdays and they begin next week (on January 28). The class will have a webcast. However, we will NOT offer alternative exam times.

The updated class website is now live: https://people.eecs.berkeley.edu/~jrs/189/

The Piazza group is open for enrollment: https://piazza.com/berkeley/spring2020/compsci189289a

On getting in to the class: EECS grad students have highest priority. Undergrads are second, according to their waitlist ordering. Non-EECS grad students are last; sorry. Concurrent enrollment students have zero chance of being enrolled. Students hoping to be enrolled should attend and submit homeworks, of course, until they know whether they'll get in. Unenrolled auditors who just want to watch lectures on machine learning are welcome to attend, but please don't submit homeworks (our grading resources are limited).

I'm looking forward to seeing you all this evening!
